OL,7,FCommenting on the study, Professor Tim
OL,8,FLenton, director of the Global Systems
OL,9,FInstitute at University of Exeter,
OL,10,Fsaid: "The research makes a convincing
OL,11,Fcase that the Amoc is approaching a
OL,12,Ftipping point based on a robust,
OL,13,Fphysically-based early warning
OL,14,Findicator.J"What it cannot ` and does
OL,15,Fnot ` say is how close the tipping
OL,16,Fpoint, because as it shows that there
OL,17,Fis insufficient data to make a
OL,18,Fstatistically reliable estimate of
OL,19,Fthat. We have to plan for the worst.
OL,20,F"We should invest in collecting
OL,21,Frelevant data and improving estimation
OL,22,Fof how close a tipping point is,
OL,23,Fimproving assessment of what its
OL,24,Fimpacts would be, and getting pre-
OL,25,Fprepared for how we could best manage
OL,26,Fand adapt to those impacts if they
